22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228111%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20data%20center%20under%20construction.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6841eb7d9d73a0031e8df8f9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225410%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0A%20data%20center%20under%20construction%20in%20Chandler%2C%20Arizona.%3Cp%3EJesse%20Rieser%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETech%20companies%20are%20spending%20hundreds%20of%20billions%20of%20dollars%20building%20data%20centers%2C%20racing%20to%20power%20an%20AI%20revolution%20they%20say%20will%20bring%20broad%20benefits%20and%20enormous%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20actual%20price%2C%20though%2C%20has%20never%20been%20fully%20measured.%20So%20a%20team%20of%20Business%20Insider%20reporters%20and%20editors%20set%20out%20to%20find%20the%20true%20cost%20of%20the%20US%20data%20center%20boom%20%E2%80%94%20in%20water%2C%20power%2C%20pollution%2C%20and%20tax%20incentives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20pulled%20obscure%20state%20records%2C%20scoured%20corporate%20disclosures%2C%20and%20sought%20analysis%20and%20guidance%20from%20government%20researchers%20in%20Virginia%20and%20elsewhere.%20We%20spoke%20to%20engineering%20specialists%20who%20study%20data%20centers%2C%20including%20Shaolei%20Ren%20at%20the%20University%20of%20California%2C%20Riverside%2C%20and%20Vijay%20Gadepally%20of%20the%20Massachusetts%20Institute%20of%20Technology.%20We%20also%20spoke%20to%20researchers%20who%20study%20incentive%20packages%2C%20such%20as%20Kasia%20Tarczynska%20of%20Good%20Jobs%20First%2C%20a%20research%20group%20that%20advocates%20for%20transparency%20and%20equality%20in%20public%20subsidies.%20And%20we%20sought%20input%20from%20companies%20and%20industry%20groups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20is%20the%20most%20complete%20accounting%20yet%20of%20data%20centers'%20impact%20on%20our%20environment%2C%20economy%2C%20and%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20we%20did%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a83f3d1-6c8d-450c-92ee-5757a8ac53e3%5C%22%3EWe%20started%20by%20identifying%20how%20many%20data%20centers%20there%20are%2C%20and%20who%20owns%20them%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20can%20never%20be%20without%20power.%20Developers%20build%20backup%20generators%20to%20provide%20emergency%20electricity.%20Since%20these%20generators%20emit%20air%20pollution%2C%20they%20are%20regulated%20by%20state%20environmental%20agencies%20and%20need%20permits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20requested%20these%20air%20permits%20and%20applications%20from%2050%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20asking%20agencies%20to%20search%20permits%20using%20federal%20industry%20codes%20associated%20with%20data%20centers.%20To%20confirm%20state%20searches%20were%20complete%2C%20Business%20Insider%20cross-referenced%20permits%20against%20company%20disclosures%2C%20news%20articles%2C%20and%20data%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdatacentermap.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edatacentermap.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbaxtel.com%2Fmap%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBaxtel%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20other%20trade%20websites.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20permits%20we%20obtained%20were%20actually%20for%20other%20types%20of%20facilities.%20If%20public%20or%20corporate%20records%20confirmed%20the%20facility%20was%20not%20a%20data%20center%2C%20we%20removed%20it%20from%20our%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20compiled%20permits%20for%201%2C240%20existing%20or%20planned%20data%20centers%20across%20the%20country%2C%20the%20most%20definitive%20tally%20to%20date.%20Tracking%20the%20year%20each%20permit%20was%20first%20issued%20reveals%20a%20construction%20boom.%20Until%202010%2C%20companies%20had%20filed%20permits%20for%20311%20data%20centers.%20By%202024%2C%20that%20number%20had%20nearly%20quadrupled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOften%20the%20permit%20holders%20are%20subsidiaries%20of%20Big%20Tech%20companies%2C%20with%20unfamiliar%20names%20like%20Nova%20Mango%20Farms.%20Business%20Insider%20determined%20the%20owners%20using%20emails%2C%20addresses%2C%20and%20other%20information%20on%20permit%20applications%2C%20secretary-of-state%20disclosures%2C%20county%20databases%2C%20and%20SEC%20filings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223d8810ed-a100-46b1-a4b7-0ad80d6f3952%5C%22%3EThen%20we%20mapped%20those%20centers'%20locations%20and%20estimated%20the%20resources%20they%20consume%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20mapped%20location%20information%20from%20the%20permits%20onto%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wri.org%2Fapplications%2Faqueduct%2Fwater-risk-atlas%2F%23%2F%3Fadvanced%3Dfalse%26basemap%3Dhydro%26indicator%3Dw_awr_def_tot_cat%26lat%3D-14.445396942837744%26lng%3D-142.85354599620152%26mapMode%3Dview%26month%3D1%26opacity%3D0.5%26ponderation%3DDEF%26predefined%3Dfalse%26projection%3Dabsolute%26scenario%3Doptimistic%26scope%3Dbaseline%26timeScale%3Dannual%26year%3Dbaseline%26zoom%3D2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAqueduct%20Water%20Risk%20Atlas%3C%2Fa%3E%20built%20by%20the%20World%20Resources%20Institute%2C%20a%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20group%20that%20advocates%20sustainability.%20The%20atlas%20measures%20a%20location's%20relative%20water%20stress%20%E2%80%94%20the%20ratio%20between%20demand%20and%20available%2C%20renewable%20supplies.%20Business%20Insider%20found%20that%2040%25%20of%20data%20centers%20were%20sited%20in%20areas%20of%20high%20or%20extremely%20high%20water%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20can%20use%20staggering%20amounts%20of%20water.%20Business%20Insider%20requested%20metered%20water%20use%20records%20and%20water%20supply%20agreements%20from%20dozens%20of%20public%20utility%20agencies%20for%20every%20data%20center%20in%20areas%20with%20extremely%20high%20water%20stress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20center%20water%20use%20is%20a%20closely%20guarded%20secret.%20Many%20agencies%20denied%20our%20requests%20for%20facility-specific%20water%20use%20or%20released%20the%20records%20only%20in%20aggregate%20for%20all%20data%20centers%20in%20a%20water%20utility's%20service%20area.%20In%20Denver%20and%20Colorado%20Springs%2C%20Colorado%2C%20utility%20agencies%20sued%20Business%20Insider%20to%20prevent%20the%20release%20of%20metered%20water%20use%20records.%20Business%20Insider%20prevailed%20in%20both%20lawsuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20found%20that%20some%20of%20the%20largest%20data%20center%20facilities%20were%20permitted%20to%20use%20more%20water%20a%20day%20than%20you%20might%20expect%20nearly%2049%2C000%20Americans%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20also%20disclose%20little%20information%20on%20how%20much%20power%20their%20US%20data%20centers%20consume.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-centers-us-power-grid-gpu-nvidia-cerebras-amazon-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EData%20center%20power%20use%3C%2Fa%3E%20varies%20based%20on%20factors%20including%20the%20types%20and%20frequency%20of%20use%20of%20servers%2C%20cooling%20systems%2C%20and%20other%20infrastructure.%20To%20account%20for%20this%2C%20Business%20Insider%20calculated%20a%20range%20of%20estimated%20annual%20data%20center%20electricity%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20calculate%20this%20range%2C%20Business%20Insider%20used%20air%20permit%20data%20to%20identify%20the%20total%20power-generation%20capacity%20of%20every%20backup%20generator%20at%20each%20facility.%20Companies%20rarely%20install%20generator%20capacity%20that%20is%20more%20than%20twice%20what%20a%20data%20center%20consumes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20often%20they%20install%20significantly%20less%20than%20that.%20So%20Business%20Insider%2C%20in%20consultation%20with%20experts%2C%20conservatively%20estimated%20that%20a%20data%20center's%20maximum%20electricity%20use%20is%20between%20half%20and%2080%25%20of%20its%20generators'%20capacity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feta-publications.lbl.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2024-12%2Flbnl-2024-united-states-data-center-energy-usage-report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20federal%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20estimates%20that%20across%20the%20industry%2C%20data%20centers%20operate%20at%20just%2050%25%20of%20that%20maximum%20electricity%20use%20level%2C%20to%20avoid%20straining%20their%20equipment.%20So%20Business%20Insider%20multiplied%20the%20low%20and%20high%20ends%20of%20its%20initial%20range%20by%2050%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider's%20data%20includes%20permits%20for%20data%20centers%20that%20are%20not%20yet%20built%20and%20fully%20online%2C%20and%20therefore%20estimates%20expected%20electricity%20use%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20If%20all%20permitted%20data%20centers%20go%20online%2C%20we%20estimate%2C%20they%20will%20use%20between%20149.6%20terawatt-hours%20and%20239.3%20terawatt-hours%20a%20year.%20Business%20Insider's%20low-end%20estimate%20is%20roughly%20equivalent%20to%20the%20state%20of%20Ohio's%20electricity%20needs%20in%202023%2C%20and%20on%20the%20high%20end%2C%20is%20nearly%20as%20much%20power%20as%20the%20entire%20state%20of%20Florida%20used%20that%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20estimates%20are%20conservative.%20The%20low%20end%20of%20our%20estimate%20is%20below%20the%20federal%20report's%20estimate%20for%20data%20center%20power%20use%20in%202023.%20The%20federal%20report%20estimates%20data%20center%20power%20use%20could%20reach%20the%20upper%20end%20of%20our%20estimate%20by%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20used%20the%20range%20average%20to%20identify%20the%20322%20largest%20facilities%20in%20our%20dataset%20that%2C%20according%20to%20our%20estimate%2C%20consume%2040%20megawatt-hours%20of%20electricity%20or%20more%20an%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Amazon%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20methodology%20%26quot%3Boversimplifies%20complex%20data%20center%20operations%20and%20is%20based%20on%20assumptions%20that%20do%20not%20account%20for%20important%20differences%20in%20how%20companies%20build%20and%20operate%20data%20centers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20and%20Meta%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Business%20Insider's%20queries%20about%20data%20center%20power%20use%20estimates%2C%20and%20QTS%20declined%20to%20comment.%20A%20Microsoft%20spokesperson%20acknowledged%20that%20its%20data%20centers%20%26quot%3Bdo%20not%20always%20run%20at%20100%25%20of%20their%20installed%20capacity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENineteen%20permits%20across%2010%20states%20%E2%80%94%20including%2012%20held%20by%20Google%20%E2%80%94%20have%20their%20generator%20capacity%20information%20fully%20or%20partially%20redacted%20under%20public%20disclosure%20exemptions%20for%20trade%20secrets.%20Business%20Insider%20was%20unable%20to%20estimate%20the%20electricity%20use%20of%20these%20facilities%2C%20so%20our%20estimate%20likely%20undercounts%20the%20true%20total.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224ee64035-8a4c-4e34-ab70-67b53ab3af47%5C%22%3ENext%2C%20we%20calculated%20data%20centers'%20likely%20public%20health%20and%20environmental%20impact%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20uses%20highly%20polluting%20fossil-fuel-fired%20sources%20for%20at%20least%2060%25%20of%20its%20electricity.%20Data%20centers%20draw%20power%20from%20a%20wide%20regional%20grid%2C%20so%20Business%20Insider%20needed%20to%20estimate%20the%20public%20health%20impact%20attributable%20to%20data%20centers'%20use%20of%20electricity%20generated%20from%20far-away%20power%20plants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20electricity%20grid%20is%20complex%20and%20does%20not%20map%20closely%20to%20state%20boundaries.%20To%20model%20the%20complexity%20of%20the%20US%20electricity%20grid%2C%20Business%20Insider%20used%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Favert%2Favert-web-edition%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEnvironmental%20Protection%20Agency%20tool%20called%20AVERT%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20splits%20the%20contiguous%2048%20states%20into%2014%20independent%20electricity%20regions%20that%20approximate%20grid%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20our%20estimate%20for%20data%20center%20power%20consumption%2C%20along%20with%20US%20Energy%20Information%20Administration%20data%20and%20the%20AVERT%20tool%2C%20Business%20Insider%20calculated%20the%20likely%20share%20of%20total%20power%20use%20attributable%20to%20data%20centers%20in%20each%20of%20these%2014%20regions.%20Then%2C%20using%20another%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcobra.epa.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEPA%20tool%20with%20the%20acronym%20COBRA%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Business%20Insider%20estimated%20the%20public%20health%20cost%20engendered%20by%20that%20share%20of%20total%20electricity-generation-related%20pollution%20in%20each%20region.%20Even%20a%20careful%20calculation%20like%20this%20is%20inherently%20imperfect%2C%20but%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20industry%20transparency%20about%20such%20emissions%20it%20provides%20a%20rare%20and%20well-founded%20estimate%20of%20the%20health%20costs%20of%20the%20data%20center%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20estimated%20that%20annual%20public%20health%20costs%20from%20electricity%20generation%20for%20data%20centers%20could%20reach%20between%20%245.7%20billion%20and%20%249.2%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPower%20plants%20are%20not%20the%20only%20source%20of%20data%20center%20air%20pollution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20diesel%20backup%20generators%20installed%20at%20data%20centers%20emit%20volatile%20organic%20compounds%2C%20nitrous%20oxides%2C%20sulfur%20dioxides%2C%20and%20particulate%20matter%20%E2%80%94%20all%20regulated%20air%20pollutants%20the%20EPA%20labels%20as%20hazardous%20to%20human%20health.%20Air%20permits%20issued%20to%20these%20facilities%20set%20total%20annual%20pollutant%20emission%20limits%20that%20determine%20how%20frequently%20their%20generators%20can%20be%20used.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20generally%20run%20their%20generators%20infrequently%20so%20emit%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20pollutants%20their%20permits%20allow.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjlarc.virginia.gov%2Flanding-2024-data-centers-in-virginia.asp%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2024%20report%20to%20the%20state%20legislature%20in%20Virginia%20%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20home%20to%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20US%20data%20centers%20with%20permits%20%E2%80%94%20calculated%20that%20data%20center%20backup%20generators%20on%20average%20emit%207%25%20of%20their%20permitted%20pollution%20limits%20each%20year.%20Business%20Insider%20used%20that%20percentage%20to%20estimate%20each%20county's%20air%20pollutant%20emissions%20from%20data%20center%20backup%20generators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20then%20input%20these%20county-by-county%20totals%20into%20COBRA%2C%20which%20models%20how%20air%20pollution%20emitted%20in%20a%20county%20affects%20public%20health%20nationwide.%20The%20tool%20assigns%20a%20dollar%20figure%20to%20what%20it%20would%20cost%20to%20avoid%20negative%20health%20outcomes%20like%20premature%20deaths%2C%20asthma%20attacks%2C%20heart%20attacks%2C%20and%20missed%20school%20or%20work%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20COBRA%20tool%20estimated%20that%20air%20pollutants%20emitted%20by%20data%20centers%20across%20the%20country%20could%20trigger%20nearly%2020%2C000%20asthma%20symptom%20cases%20a%20year%20and%20create%20a%20%24385%20million%20annual%20burden%20on%20public%20health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenerator%20pollution%20is%20more%20harmful%20to%20communities%20already%20overburdened%20by%20environmental%20pollutants.%20A%20community%20that%20already%20has%20high%20levels%20of%20air%20pollution%20will%20experience%20greater%20negative%20health%20impacts%20from%20additional%20pollutants%2C%20for%20example%2C%20than%20a%20community%20that%20isn't%20already%20saturated%20with%20harmful%20pollutants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20better%20understand%20their%20impact%20on%20these%20communities%2C%20Business%20Insider%20mapped%20all%201%2C240%20data%20center%20locations%20onto%20a%20third%20EPA%20tool%20called%20EJ%20Screen%20that%20combines%20census%20and%20pollutant%20data%20within%20a%20mile%20radius%20of%20a%20specified%20location.%20We%20found%20that%20more%20than%20230%20data%20center%20locations%20were%20in%20communities%20highly%20overburdened%20by%20environmental%20pollutants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228d26077f-eeba-4265-8286-cc5140a4cdfd%5C%22%3EFinally%2C%20we%20reported%20on%20data%20centers'%20impact%20on%20the%20economy%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20requested%20and%20obtained%20the%20most%20detailed%20data-center-related%20economic%20development%20deals%20and%20annual%20tax%20incentive%20disclosures%20for%20facilities%20in%20and%20around%20Columbus%2C%20Ohio.%20Some%20of%20the%20oldest%20data%20center%20deals%20in%20the%20state%20are%20in%20Franklin%20and%20Licking%20counties%2C%20and%20companies%20are%20required%20to%20disclose%20how%20much%20they've%20saved%20from%20these%20tax%20exemption%20agreements%20each%20year%2C%20which%20made%20the%20state%20a%20useful%20case%20study%20for%20judging%20data%20centers'%20actual%20economic%20impact.%20Business%20Insider%20tallied%20these%20numbers%2C%20then%20used%20company-reported%20property%20investment%20totals%20to%20calculate%20total%20state%20and%20local%20sales%20and%20use%20tax%20savings%20(7.5%25%20for%20Franklin%20County%20and%205.75%25%20for%20Licking%20County).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20did%20not%20include%20personal%20property%20tax%20in%20our%20calculations%2C%20as%20Ohio%20eliminated%20that%20tax.%20Because%20of%20fluctuations%20in%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20employed%20at%20data%20centers%2C%20Business%20Insider%20also%20did%20not%20include%20state%20or%20local%20job%20creation%20tax%20credits%20in%20the%20analysis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20nevertheless%20found%20that%20these%20tax%20incentive%20packages%20given%20to%20tech%20companies%20were%20highly%20lucrative%2C%20amounting%20to%20as%20much%20as%20%242%20million%20in%20tax%20savings%20per%20full%20time%20job%20at%20a%20data%20center.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Caside%3E%5Cn%3Ch4%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223f2fb3e4-59ce-4010-be97-181a030f0a03%5C%22%3ESeries%20credits%3C%2Fh4%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReporting%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHannah%20Beckler%2C%20Dakin%20Campbell%2C%20Daniel%20Geiger%2C%20Rosemarie%20Ho%2C%20Narimes%20Parakul%2C%20Adam%20Rogers%2C%20Ellen%20Thomas%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EEditing%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Jeffrey%20Cane%2C%20Rosalie%20Chan%2C%20Jason%20Dean%2C%20Esther%20Kaplan%2C%20Jake%20Swearingen%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EResearch%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Darren%20Ankrom%2C%20Schuyler%20Mitchell%2C%20Trey%20Strange%2C%20Yuheng%20Zhan%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDesign%20and%20visuals%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Dan%20DeLorenzo%2C%20Isabel%20Fernandez-Pujol%2C%20Jinpeng%20Li%2C%20Kim%20Nguyen%2C%20Randy%20Yeip%2C%20Rebecca%20Zisser%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPhotography%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Kendrick%20Brinson%2C%20John%20David-Richardson%2C%20Greg%20Kahn%2C%20Brian%20Palmer%2C%20Jesse%20Rieser%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVideo%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Robert%20Leslie%2C%20Gary%20Moon%2C%20Marco%20Secci%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECopy%20editing%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Mark%20Abadi%2C%20Kevin%20Kaplan%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Faside%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-calculate-data-center-cost-environmental-impact-methodology-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750147981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6841ebc89b2a601d01b26946%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-calculate-data-center-cost-environmental-impact-methodology-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22How%20Business%20Insider%20calculated%20data%20centers'%20true%20cost%2C%20from%20their%20electricity%20and%20water%20use%20to%20their%20impact%20on%20the%20environment%20and%20public%20health.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22hbeckler%40insider.com%20(Hannah%20Beckler%2CRosemarie%20Ho%2CNarimes%20Parakul%2CDakin%20Campbell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-calculate-data-center-cost-environmental-impact-methodology-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20the%20billion-dollar%20war%20over%20'peace%20tech'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cofounder%20Arvid%20Bell%20on%20a%20blue%20background%20with%20the%20peace%20dove%20on%20his%20right%20and%20a%20bomb%20on%20his%20left%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6850719b3d5881a51c1b81a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Arvid%20Bell%2C%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Ava%20Horton%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20second%20annual%20AI%2B%20Expo%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20in%20early%20June%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fisrael-strikes-iran-nuclear-program-response-war-risk-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewar%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20word%20of%20the%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20mix%20of%20Beltway%20bureaucrats%2C%20military%20personnel%2C%20and%20Washington's%20consultant%20class%20peruse%20the%20expansive%20Walter%20E.%20Washington%20Convention%20Center%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-tech-founders-skipping-college-new-dropping-out-palantir-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPalantir%3C%2Fa%3E%20booth%20showcases%20its%20latest%20in%20data-collection%20suites%20for%20%26quot%3Bwarfighters.%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwisconsin-lawmaker-pushes-f-35-noise-relief-new-noise-complaint-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELockheed%20Martin%3C%2Fa%3E%20touts%20the%20many%20ways%20it%20is%20implementing%20AI%20throughout%20its%20weaponry%20systems.%20On%20the%20soundstage%2C%20the%20defense%20tech%20darling%20Mach%20Industries%20is%20selling%20its%20newest%20uncrewed%20aerial%20vehicles.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20living%20in%20a%20world%20with%20great-power%20competition%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20presenter%20says.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can't%20rule%20out%20the%20possibility%20of%20war%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20best%20way%20to%20prevent%20a%20war%20is%20deterrence%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20flanked%20by%20videos%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoo-many-companies-want-sell-small-aerial-drones-us-military-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrones%20flying%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20what%20looked%20like%20the%20rugged%20mountains%20and%20valleys%20of%20Kandahar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHosted%20by%20the%20Special%20Competitive%20Studies%20Project%2C%20a%20think%20tank%20led%20by%20former%20Google%20CEO%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feric-schmidt-ex-google-ceo-ai-book-kissinger-white-stork-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEric%20Schmidt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20expo%20says%20it%20seeks%20to%20bridge%20the%20gap%20between%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-idolize-youth-ai-changing-tech-hiring-signalfire-genz-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESilicon%20Valley%20entrepreneurs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Washington%20policymakers%20to%20%26quot%3Bstrengthen%26quot%3B%20America%20and%20its%20allies'%20%26quot%3Bcompetitiveness%20in%20critical%20technologies.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20floor%20below%2C%20a%20startup%20called%20Anadyr%20Horizon%20is%20making%20a%20very%20different%20sales%20pitch%2C%20for%20software%20that%20seeks%20to%20prevent%20war%20rather%20than%20fight%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BPeace%20tech%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20company's%20cofounder%20Arvid%20Bell%20calls%20it.%20Dressed%20in%20white%20khakis%20and%20a%20black%20pinstripe%20suit%20jacket%20with%20a%20dove%20and%20olive%20branch%20pinned%20to%20his%20lapel%20(a%20gift%20from%20his%20husband)%2C%20the%20former%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-trump-visa-crackdown-applications-european-universities-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHarvard%3C%2Fa%3E%20political%20scientist%20begins%20by%20noting%20that%20Russia's%20all-out%20invasion%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-pay-civilians-shoot-down-drones-own-guns-cars-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUkraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20come%20as%20a%20surprise%20to%20many%20political%20scientists.%20But%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-meta-ai-chatbot-discover-feed-depressing-why-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20he%20says%2C%20could%20predict%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELong%20the%20domain%20of%20fantasy%20and%20science%20fiction%2C%20the%20idea%20of%20forecasting%20conflict%20has%20now%20become%20a%20serious%20pursuit.%20In%20Isaac%20Asimov's%201950s%20%26quot%3BFoundation%26quot%3B%20series%2C%20the%20main%20character%20develops%20an%20algorithm%20that%20allows%20him%20to%20predict%20the%20decline%20of%20the%20Galactic%20Empire%2C%20angering%20its%20rulers%20and%20forcing%20him%20into%20exile.%20During%20the%20coronavirus%20pandemic%2C%20the%20US%20State%20Department%20experimented%20with%20AI%20fed%20with%20Twitter%20data%20to%20predict%20%26quot%3BCOVID%20cases%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bviolent%20events.%26quot%3B%20In%20its%20AI%20audit%20two%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstate-department-buy-400-million-worth-armored-teslas-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EState%20Department%3C%2Fa%3E%20revealed%20that%20it%20started%20training%20AI%20on%20%26quot%3Bopen-source%20political%2C%20social%2C%20and%20economic%20datasets%26quot%3B%20to%20predict%20%26quot%3Bmass%20civilian%20killings.%26quot%3B%20The%20UN%20is%20also%20said%20to%20have%20experimented%20with%20AI%20to%20model%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchaos-erupts-after-thousands-palestinians-rush-to-grab-aid-gaza-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewar%20in%20Gaza%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInterest%20in%20AI's%20ability%20to%20anticipate%20humanity's%20most%20destructive%20urges%20comes%20as%20the%20world%20sees%20an%20alarming%20rise%20in%20global%20conflict.%20Last%20week%2C%20Israel%20launched%20strikes%20against%20Tehran%20under%20the%20pretense%20that%20the%20Ayatollah%20was%20inching%20closer%20to%20developing%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fimages-show-damage-iran-nuclear-facility-after-israel-strikes-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enuclear%20bomb%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20month%20ago%2C%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20came%20to%20the%20brink%20of%20war%20over%20the%20decadeslong%20dispute%20in%20Kashmir.%20The%20ongoing%20Gaza%20conflict%20has%20claimed%20more%20than%2050%2C000%20lives%2C%20and%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20more%20than%20150%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20conservative%20estimates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnadyr%20Horizon%20believes%20it%20can%20prevent%20war%20by%20using%20AI%20to%20create%20facsimiles%20of%20world%20leaders%20that%20live%20and%20interact%20in%20a%20simulation%20of%20the%20real%20world.%20Its%20software%2C%20North%20Star%2C%20is%20designed%20to%20predict%20how%20real-world%20decision-makers%20might%20react%20to%20a%20given%20situation%20or%20stimuli%20%E2%80%94%20like%20economic%20sanctions%20or%20a%20naval%20blockade%20%E2%80%94%20by%20observing%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-agents-study-company-run-by-ai-disaster-replace-jobs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20counterparts%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Bell%20says%20these%20digital%20twins%20are%20so%20sophisticated%20that%20they%20can%20emulate%20how%20a%20leader%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fputin-business-allies-oppose-return-western-companies-russia-mcdonalds-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVladimir%20Putin%3C%2Fa%3E%20might%20behave%20when%20he's%20sleep%20deprived%20versus%20having%20gotten%20a%20full%20night's%20rest.%20(Much%20of%20the%20formula%20behind%20these%20scores%20is%20Anadyr%20Horizon's%20secret%20sauce%2C%20but%20the%20Russian%20autocrat%20has%20boasted%20that%20he%20gets%20by%20on%20four%20hours%20of%20sleep.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20screen%2C%20North%20Star%20looks%20like%20the%201970s%20video%20game%20%26quot%3BThe%20Oregon%20Trail%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20reams%20of%20text%20chronicling%20events%20from%20the%20simulated%20world.%20Bell%20demonstrates%20by%20prompting%20it%20to%20show%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20the%20United%20States%20imposed%20a%20no-fly%20zone%20over%20Ukraine%20%E2%80%94%20a%20maneuver%20with%20a%20mixed%20history%20(e.g.%2C%20effective%20in%20preventing%20Saddam%20Hussein's%20regime%20from%20carpet-bombing%20southern%20Iraq%20in%201991%3B%20ineffective%20in%20preventing%20the%20Srebrenica%20massacre%20of%201995).%20North%20Star%20then%20runs%20thousands%20of%20simulations%2C%20each%20its%20own%20multiverse%20with%20slightly%20different%20variables%2C%20from%20whether%20a%20key%20decision-maker%20was%20late%20to%20work%20to%20the%20order%20in%20which%20a%20single%20conversation%20over%20military%20strategy%20might%20happen.%20It%20can%20model%20the%20outcomes%20of%20multiple%20different%20policies%2C%20and%20even%20offer%20advice%20on%20which%20leaders%20might%20be%20open%20to%20back%20channel%20negotiations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%20the%20program%20spits%20out%20a%20result%3A%20Russia%20is%2060%25%20likely%20to%20escalate%20the%20conflict%20if%20a%20no-fly%20zone%20is%20imposed.%20It%20also%20provides%20a%20hypothetical%20SVR%20intelligence%20brief%20describing%20Russia's%20devastating%20escalation.%20%26quot%3BOver%20the%20past%2024%20hours%2C%20we%20have%20delivered%20high-precision%20strikes%20on%20enemy%20troop%20concentrations%20and%20military%20equipment%2C%20destroying%20ammunition%20depots%2C%20communication%20hubs%2C%20and%20infrastructure%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Bell%2C%20the%20origins%20of%20Anadyr%20Horizon%20were%20relatively%20low-tech.%20Back%20when%20he%20was%20a%20lecturer%20at%20Harvard%20%E2%80%94%20teaching%20courses%20in%20conflict%20de-escalation%20and%20post-Soviet%20geopolitics%20%E2%80%94%20he%20used%20funds%20from%20the%20university's%20startup%20incubator%2C%20the%20Scholar-Entrepreneur%20Initiative%2C%20to%20launch%20an%20organization%20that%20held%20a%20yearly%20war%20gaming%20event%20with%20high-profile%20representatives%20from%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20European%20Union.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMilitary%20and%20diplomatic%20leaders%20would%20join%20Bell%20in%20Cambridge%20and%20be%20assigned%20the%20role%20of%20a%20foreign%20dignitary%20%E2%80%94%20Gen.%20Zhang%20Youxia%2C%20the%20vice%20chairman%20of%20China's%20Central%20Military%20Commission%2C%20say.%20For%20three%20days%20of%20the%20event%2C%20they%20would%20become%20method%20actors%20going%20to%20painstaking%20lengths%20to%20re-create%20the%20lives%20of%20their%20assigned%20leaders%20as%20realistically%20as%20possible%2C%20wearing%20the%20same%20military%20fatigues%2C%20chauffeured%20in%20their%20preferred%20cars%2C%20and%20conferring%20in%20a%20replica%20of%20their%20situation%20room.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20theater%2C%26quot%3B%20Bell%20tells%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBell%2C%20who'd%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fyoutube-afghanistan-tiktok-adventure-taliban-tourism-influencers-ak47s-selfie-sticks-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraveling%20to%20Afghanistan%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20Ph.D.%20researcher%20over%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20drew%20from%20his%20experience%20studying%20breakdowns%20in%20negotiations%20during%20armed%20conflict.%20His%20goal%20was%20to%20have%20participants%20empathize%20with%20those%20they%20might%20otherwise%20see%20as%20their%20adversary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222875%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Negotiation%20Task%20Force%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685085ca85e81483682c32ea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221619%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20senior%20military%20official%20who%20participated%20in%20a%20wargaming%20event%20at%20Harvard%20is%20greeted%20by%20another%20in%20a%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20uniform.%3Cp%3ENegotiation%20Task%20Force%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20one%20such%20event%20in%20December%202021%2C%20the%20Russian%20team%20invaded%20Ukraine%20using%20the%20exact%20multipronged%20military%20assault%20that%20Putin%20would%20use%2075%20days%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20later%2C%20he%20was%20introduced%20to%20Ferenc%20Dalnoki-Veress%2C%20a%20Nobel%20Prize-winning%20physicist%2C%20through%20Bill%20Potter%2C%20the%20founding%20director%20of%20the%20James%20Martin%20Center%20for%20Nonproliferation%20Studies%20at%20Middlebury%20College.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Dalnoki-Veress%20was%20experimenting%20with%20prompting%20different%20AI%20agents%20to%20debate%20each%20other.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20something%20stupid%2C%26quot%3B%20Dalnoki-Veress%20says.%20%26quot%3BLike%20one%20agent%20has%20to%20prove%20to%20the%20other%20agent%20that%20cherry%20lollipops%20are%20better%20than%20lemon%20lollipops.%26quot%3B%20Dalnoki-Veress%20was%20impressed%20by%20the%20lengths%20that%20the%20robots%20would%20go%20to%20convince%20the%20others%20of%20their%20position.%20Sometimes%20they'd%20even%20lie%20to%20each%20other%20%E2%80%94%20if%20prompted%20to%20win%20at%20all%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESoon%20he%20started%20experimenting%20with%20whether%20the%20agents%20would%20collaborate%2C%20negotiate%2C%20or%20even%20write%20treaties%20with%20one%20another.%20%26quot%3BIt%20occurred%20to%20me%20how%20human%20it%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Dalnoki-Veress.%20Last%20fall%2C%20the%20trio%20of%20academics%20founded%20Anadyr%20with%20the%20belief%20they%20could%20imbue%20these%20bots%20with%20the%20personalities%20of%20world%20leaders%20and%20realistically%20emulate%20their%20interactions.%20Instead%20of%20organizing%20one%20war%20game%20a%20year%2C%20they%20could%20game%20out%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20scenarios%20over%20the%20course%20of%20one%20night%20and%20get%20%26quot%3Bprobabilistic%20estimates%20of%20where%20conflicts%20are%20really%20going%20to%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Bell%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20hopes%20North%20Star's%20predictive%20capabilities%20will%20help%20diplomats%20and%20politicians%20make%20better%20decisions%20about%20how%20to%20negotiate%20during%20times%20of%20conflict%20and%20even%20prevent%20wars.%20Anadyr%20is%20a%20reference%20to%20the%20code%20name%20the%20USSR%20used%20for%20its%20deployment%20of%20ballistic%20missiles%20and%20warfighters%20to%20the%20western%20coasts%20of%20Cuba%20in%20October%201962.%20If%20President%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20had%20a%20tool%20like%20North%20Star%20to%20preempt%20the%20Cuban%20Missile%20Crisis%2C%20Bell%20posits%2C%20instead%20of%20having%2013%20days%20to%20respond%2C%20he%20might%20have%20had%20six%20months.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20reclaiming%20this%20name%20to%20say%2C%20'OK%2C%20the%20next%20Operation%20Anadyr%2C%20we%20will%20detect%20early%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20the%20company%20and%20its%20venture%20capital%20backers%20believe%20it%20can%20make%20billions.%20By%20some%20estimates%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.economicsandpeace.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F06%2FGPI-2024-web.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eviolent%20conflict%20cost%20the%20global%20economy%20%2419%20trillion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%20alone.%20And%20one%20study%20conducted%20by%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20suggests%20every%20dollar%20spent%20on%20conflict%20prevention%20can%20yield%20a%20return%20as%20high%20as%20%24103%20in%20countries%20that%20have%20recently%20experienced%20violent%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeace%20tech%20is%20going%20after%20a%20huge%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Brian%20Abrams%2C%20a%20founder%20of%20B%20Ventures%2C%20an%20investor%20in%20Anadyr.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20climate%20tech%2C%20a%20decade%20ago%2C%20the%20space%20was%20very%20small.%20It%20wasn't%20even%20called%20climate%20tech%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20adds.%20%26quot%3BNow%2C%20climate%20tech%20sees%20about%20%2450%20billion%20in%20investment%20annually.%26quot%3B%20He%20says%20peace%20tech%20can%20replicate%20the%20growth%20seen%20in%20the%20climate%20tech%20industry.%20Anadyr's%20early%20clients%20aren't%20confined%20to%20just%20state%20agencies%3B%20the%20company%20is%20also%20selling%20its%20software%20to%20corporate%20risk%20managers%20who%20want%20to%20understand%20how%20social%20unrest%20might%20affect%20their%20investments%20and%20assets%20in%20different%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnadyr%20has%20also%20raised%20funds%20from%20Commonweal%20Ventures%2C%20an%20early%20investor%20in%20the%20defense%20contractor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpalantir-stock-price-pltr-alex-karp-ai-government-retail-traders-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPalantir%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20AIN%20Ventures%2C%20a%20veteran-led%20firm%20that%20invests%20in%20technologies%20that%20can%20be%20useful%20in%20both%20the%20military%20and%20in%20the%20private%20sector.%20Bell%20says%20they've%20already%20been%20able%20to%20close%20a%20seven-figure%20pre-seed%20round%2C%20though%20he%20didn't%20disclose%20the%20exact%20figures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20a%20company%20dedicated%20to%20preventing%20war%20had%20chosen%20a%20defense%20expo%20to%20unveil%20its%20product%20wasn't%20lost%20on%20Bell.%20But%20the%20lines%20between%20peace%20and%20war%20technology%20are%20blurrier%20than%20they%20may%20seem.%20The%20defense%20contractor%20Rhombus%20Power%2C%20a%20sponsor%20of%20the%20expo%2C%20has%20its%20own%20AI%20conflict%20prediction%20software%20that%20it%20says%20made%20accurate%20predictions%20of%20Russia's%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20%26quot%3BWe%20look%20at%20peace%20tech%20as%20the%20flip%20side%20of%20the%20same%20coin%2C%26quot%3B%20Abrams%20says.%20According%20to%20Abrams%2C%20the%20size%20of%20the%20defense%20industry%20shows%20that%20there%20is%20a%20market%20for%20technology%20seeking%20to%20prevent%20war.%20%26quot%3BThe%20difference%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says%2C%20between%20peace%20tech%20and%20war%20tech%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20different%20approach%20to%20the%20same%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20audience%20at%20Bell's%20demo%20had%20its%20fair%20share%20of%20defense%20tech%20funders%20in%20attendance.%20When%20one%20of%20the%20venture%20capitalists%20in%20the%20crowd%20asks%20whether%20he's%20considered%20the%20technology's%20military%20applications%2C%20he%20tells%20them%20that's%20a%20line%20too%20far%20for%20Anadyr%20Horizon%2C%20at%20present.%20%26quot%3BFor%20now%20we're%20definitely%20focused%20on%20the%20strategic%20level%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20we're%20trying%20to%20stop%20war.%26quot%3B%20A%20savvy%20salesman%2C%20he%20adds%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20still%20early%20enough%20to%20see%20where%20the%20market%20will%20pull%20us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20lunch%2C%20I%20ask%20the%20founders%20if%20they%20believe%20something%20is%20lost%20in%20automating%20the%20war%20games%20Bell%20conducted%20at%20Harvard.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20you're%20losing%2C%26quot%3B%20Bell%20concedes%2C%20%26quot%3Bis%20the%20extremely%20personal%20and%20emotional%20experience%20of%20an%20American%20admiral%20who%20is%20put%20into%20the%20shoes%20of%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchina-as-many-icbms-as-us-russia-by-2030-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChinese%20counterpart%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20for%20the%20first%20time%20is%20looking%20at%20American%20warships%20coming%20to%20his%20coast.%26quot%3B%20But%20you%20can%20only%20run%20such%20a%20realistic%20simulation%20with%20real%20people%20a%20few%20times%20a%20year.%20%26quot%3BThe%20capabilities%20of%20AI%20are%20exponential%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20impact%20is%20on%20a%20much%20greater%20scale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20other%20challenges%20with%20using%20artificial%20intelligence%20for%20something%20as%20high-stakes%20as%20preventing%20the%20next%20world%20war.%20Researchers%20have%20long%20warned%20that%20AI%20models%20may%20hold%20biases%20hidden%20in%20the%20data%20from%20which%20they%20were%20trained.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20say%20history%20is%20written%20by%20the%20victor%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-google-researcher-openai-board-diversity-timnit-gebru-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETimnit%20Gebru%2C%20an%20AI%20researcher%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20fled%20Eritrea%20in%201998%2C%20during%20the%20country's%20war%20with%20Ethiopia.%20An%20AI%20system%20trained%20on%20open-source%20information%20on%20the%20internet%2C%20she%20says%2C%20will%20inherently%20represent%20the%20biases%20of%20the%20most%20online%20groups%20%E2%80%94%20which%20tend%20to%20be%20Western%20or%20European.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20notion%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20use%20a%20lot%20of%20data%20on%20the%20internet%20and%20therefore%20represent%20some%20sort%20of%20unbiased%20truth%20is%20already%20fraught%2C%26quot%3B%20Gebru%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20founders%20are%20unwilling%20to%20reveal%20the%20actual%20data%20their%20digital%20world%20leaders%20are%20trained%20on%2C%20but%20they%20do%20offer%20that%20Anadyr%20Horizon%20uses%20%26quot%3Bproprietary%20datasets%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-openai-ai-dictionary-help-understand-nvidia-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopen-source%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20coded%20behavioral%20inputs%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20they%20go%20to%20great%20lengths%20to%20use%20books%20and%20data%20from%20outside%20the%20English-speaking%20world%20to%20account%20for%20differing%20world%20views.%20The%20leaders%20they%20emulate%2C%20Bell%20says%2C%20use%20as%20many%20as%20150%20datapoints.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBiases%20in%20these%20new%20AI%20systems%20are%20especially%20hard%20to%20interrogate%20not%20only%20because%20of%20this%20lack%20of%20transparency%20around%20the%20data%20used%20by%20the%20systems%2C%20but%20also%20because%20of%20how%20the%20chatbots%20interpret%20that%20information.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20generative%20AI%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworld-model-ai-explained-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eintelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20is%20a%20misnomer%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20essentially%20spitting%20out%20a%20likely%20sequence%20of%20words%2C%26quot%3B%20Gebru%20says.%20This%20is%20why%20bots%20are%20so%20prone%20to%20confidently%20expressing%20falsehoods.%20They%20don't%20actually%20know%20what%20they're%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20hard%20to%20trace%20why%20they%20make%20certain%20decisions.%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnvidia-brands-using-ai-boost-marketing-delta-unilever-mars-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENeural%20networks%3C%2Fa%3E%20aren't%20explainable%2C%26quot%3B%20Gebru%20says.%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20like%20a%20regression%20model%20where%20you%20can%20go%20back%20and%20see%20how%20and%20why%20it%20made%20predictions%20in%20certain%20ways.%26quot%3B%20One%20study%20into%20the%20use%20of%20large%20language%20models%20for%20diplomatic%20decision-making%2C%20conducted%20last%20year%20by%20researchers%20at%20Stanford%2C%20found%20that%20AI%20models%20tended%20to%20be%20warmongers.%20%26quot%3BIt%20appears%20LLM-based%20agents%20tended%20to%20equate%20increased%20military%20spending%20and%20deterrent%20behavior%20with%20an%20increase%20in%20power%20and%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BIn%20some%20cases%2C%20this%20tendency%20even%20led%20to%20decisions%20to%20execute%20a%20full%20nuclear%20attack%20in%20order%20to%20de-escalate%20conflicts.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20trigger-happy%20AI%20system%20could%20have%20severe%20consequences%20in%20the%20real%20world.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20hedge%20funds%20or%20corporations%20act%20collectively%20on%20a%20prediction%20from%20a%20tool%20like%20North%20Star%20that%20a%20country%20in%20which%20they%20have%20heavily%20invested%20is%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20collapse%2C%20and%20they%20preemptively%20sell%20off%20their%20assets%2C%20it%20may%20lead%20to%20the%20very%20situation%20the%20system%20had%20predicted%20%E2%80%94%20the%20mass%20exodus%20of%20capital%20actually%20causing%20currency%20depreciation%2C%20unemployment%2C%20and%20liquidity%20crises.%20%26quot%3BThe%20claim%20that%20a%20place%20is%20unstable%2C%20will%20make%20it%20unstable%2C%26quot%3B%20Gebru%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20that%20problem%20seems%20academic%20to%20Bell.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20bit%20like%20a%20philosophical%20or%20ethical%20problem.%20Like%20the%20butterfly%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20we'll%20have%20to%20wrestle%20with%20it%20at%20some%20point.%26quot%3B%20He%20insists%20they%20aren't%20the%20typical%20%26quot%3Bmove%20fast%2C%20break%20things%26quot%3B%20tech%20company.%20They're%20deliberate%20about%20consulting%20with%20subject-area%20experts%20as%20they%20model%20different%20countries%20and%20world%20leaders%2C%20he%20says%2C%20and%20have%20released%20the%20product%20to%20only%20a%20select%20list%20of%20firms.%20%26quot%3BI%20want%20to%20simulate%20what%20breaks%20the%20world.%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20break%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJon%20Danilowicz%2C%20a%20former%20senior%20diplomat%20who%20served%20in%20South%20Sudan%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20Bangladesh%2C%20notes%20the%20inherent%20unpredictability%20of%20war%2C%20with%20contingencies%20and%20factors%20that%20can't%20always%20be%20accounted%20for.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20what's%20going%20to%20happen%20with%20Israel%20taking%20action%20against%20Iran's%20nuclear%20program%2C%20you%20can%20do%20all%20kinds%20of%20scenarios%20on%20how%20that's%20going%20to%20play%20out.%20I'm%20sure%20there's%20somebody%20who's%20going%20to%20make%20a%20prediction%2C%20which%20after%20the%20fact%20they'll%20be%20able%20to%20say%20they%20were%20right.%20But%20what%20about%20the%20multiples%20that%20got%20it%20totally%20wrong%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20never%20certainty%20in%20these%20kinds%20of%20decision-making%20situations%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Bell.%20%26quot%3BIn%20some%20senses%2C%20we%20can't%20predict%20the%20future.%20But%20we%20can%20assign%20probabilities.%20Then%20it's%20up%20to%20the%20user%20to%20decide%20what%20to%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20meantime%2C%20the%20company%20has%20more%20pressing%20problems.%20Like%20many%20startups%20building%20on%20top%20of%20generative%20AI%20models%2C%20the%20costs%20to%20run%20North%20Star%20are%20huge.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20want%20to%20give%20you%20a%20figure%2C%20but%20if%20you%20knew%2C%20you'd%20drop%20your%20fork.%20It's%20extremely%20expensive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20On%20top%20of%20that%2C%20contracting%20with%20the%20government%20and%20receiving%20the%20necessary%20clearances%20can%20be%20its%20own%20set%20of%20bureaucratic%20red%20tape%20and%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20no%20shortage%20of%20interest%20in%20their%20technology.%20As%20I%20leave%20Bell%20and%20Dalnoki-Veress%2C%20they%20rush%20off%20to%20another%20meeting%3A%20Eric%20Schmidt's%20office%20wanted%20a%20private%20demonstration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Ftekendra-parmar%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ETeken